%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Applesauce%20pouches%20that%20gave%20children%20lead%20poisoning%20may%20have%20been%20contaminated%20on%20purpose%2C%20FDA%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221902%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Weis%20Cinnamon%20applesauce%2C%20WanaBana%20apple%20cinnamon%20fruit%20puree%20and%20Schnuck's%20apple%20sauce%20with%20cinnamon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657d9dd70ec98e92f75040d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221270%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWeis%20Cinnamon%20applesauce%2C%20WanaBana%20apple%20cinnamon%20fruit%20puree%20and%20Schnuck's%20apple%20sauce%20with%20cinnamon.%3Cp%3EFDA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EApplesauce%20that%20reportedly%20gave%20children%20lead%20poisoning%20may%20have%20been%20contaminated%20on%20purpose%2C%20the%20FDA%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20three%20similar%20products%20were%20recalled%20in%20November.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20pouches%20may%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%C2%A0%26quot%3Beconomically%20motivated%20adulteration%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20FDA%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EContaminated%20applesauce%20pouches%20that%20reportedly%20gave%20at%20least%2045%20children%20lead%20poisoning%20may%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Ffood%2Foutbreaks-foodborne-illness%2Finvestigation-elevated-lead-levels-cinnamon-applesauce-pouches-november-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etainted%20on%20purpose%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Food%20and%20Drug%20Administration%20said%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fsafety%2Frecalls-market-withdrawals-safety-alerts%2Fwanabana-recalls-wanabana-weis-and-schnucks-apple-cinnamon-fruit-puree-pouches-cinnamon-apple-sauce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWanaBana%20recalled%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20WanaBana%2C%20Weis%2C%20and%20Schnucks%20apple%20cinnamon%20fruit%20pur%C3%A9e%20pouches%20and%20cinnamon%20apple%20sauce%20in%20November%20due%20to%20reportedly%20elevated%20lead%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA's%20deputy%20commissioner%20for%20human%20foods%2C%20Jim%20Jones%2C%20said%20that%20signs%20point%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F12%2F14%2Fapplesauce-pouches-may-have-been-contaminated-on-purpose-fda-foods-chief-says-00131797%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintentional%20act%20on%20the%20part%20of%20someone%20in%20the%20supply%20chain%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Politico%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20added%20that%20an%20ongoing%20investigation%20seeks%20to%20uncover%20who%20may%20have%20tainted%20the%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pouches%20may%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Ffood%2Fcompliance-enforcement-food%2Feconomically-motivated-adulteration-food-fraud%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Beconomically%20motivated%20adulteration%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfood%20fraud%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20FDA%20said.%20This%20happens%20when%20a%20valuable%20ingredient%20is%20intentionally%20left%20out%2C%20taken%20out%2C%20or%20substituted%20without%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20said%20one%20example%20of%20this%20is%20when%20lead-based%20dyes%20are%20introduced%20to%20alter%20the%20color%20of%20a%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELead%20is%20toxic%20to%20humans%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Flead%2Fprevention%2Fhealth-effects.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren%20should%20be%20protected%20from%20exposure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention.%20Lead%20poisoning%20is%20not%20always%20apparent%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atsdr.cdc.gov%2Fcsem%2Fleadtoxicity%2Fsigns_and_symptoms.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20short-term%20exposure%20can%20include%20headaches%2C%20abdominal%20pain%2C%20vomiting%2C%20and%