2Fpress_releases_media_advisories%2FHUD_No_23_278%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoint-in-time%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Development%20that%20was%20released%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20number%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpdf%2F2023-AHAR-Part-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincludes%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%2035%2C000%20homeless%20veterans%2C%20making%20up%20about%207%25%20of%20all%20adults%20experiencing%20homelessness%20that%20night.%20In%20January%2C%20about%2020%2C000%20homeless%20veterans%20were%20sheltered%2C%20and%20about%2015%2C500%20were%20unsheltered.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20some%2022%20of%20every%2010%2C000%20veterans%20in%20America%20were%20homeless%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20analysis%2C%20which%20concluded%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20more%20common%20for%20veterans%20to%20experience%20homelessness%20than%20for%20all%20people%20in%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20has%20its%20limitations.%20The%20department%20has%20only%20been%20tracking%20homeless%20veterans%20since%202009%2C%20when%20there%20were%20over%2073%2C000%20homeless%20veterans%20reported%20in%20total.%20Data%20for%202020-2021%20is%20also%20incomplete%20due%20to%20data%20collection%20obstacles%20caused%20by%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20number%20of%20homeless%20vets%20from%202022%20to%202023%20spiked%20by%20the%20largest%20margin%20since%20the%20department%20began%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emeasuring%20homelessness%20using%20its%20January%20point-in-time%20analysis%20in%202009.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetween%202022%20and%202023%2C%20the%20number%20of%20veterans%20experiencing%20homelessness%20increased%20by%207%25%2C%26quot%3B%20amounting%20to%202%2C445%20additional%20veterans%2C%20the%20HUD%20analysis%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20increased%20homelessness%20is%20cause%20for%20concern%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Veterans%20Affairs%20announced%20last%20month%20that%20it%20had%20actually%20met%20its%20goal%20of%20housing%20a%20total%20of%2038%2C000%20veterans%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20we%20met%20our%20goals%20for%202023%2C%20we're%20not%20stopping%20here.%20We're%20going%20to%20keep%20pushing%20%E2%80%94%20through%20the%20end%20of%20this%20calendar%20year%20and%20beyond%20%E2%80%94%20until%20every%20Veteran%20has%20a%20safe%2C%20stable%20place%20to%20call%20home%20in%20this%20country%20they%20fought%20to%20defend%2C%26quot%3B%20Veteran%20Affairs%20Secretary%20Denis%20McDonough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomelessness-us-veterans-increase-largest-margin-yet-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702758408000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657df23c0ec98e92f7504612%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomelessness-us-veterans-increase-largest-margin-yet-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20a%20single%20day%20in%20January%20this%20year%2C%20over%20650%2C000%20people%20were%20homeless%2C%20according%20to%20a%20newly%20released%20analysis%20from%20the%20US%20government.%20Of%20those%2C%20more%20than%2035%2C000%20were%20veterans.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbalevic%40insider.com%20(Katie%20Balevic)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A43%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomelessness-us-veterans-increase-largest-margin-yet-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Viksit%20Bharat%20campaign%20now%20a%20mass%20movement%3A%20PM%20Modi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702758034000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106052724%2Cimgsize-40176.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2