20employees%20of%20doing%20nothing%20to%20prevent%20Christopher%20Ray%2C%20with%20whom%20she%20has%20a%20child%2C%20from%20dying%20by%20suicide%20inside%20the%20jail%20in%202021.%20The%20lawsuit%20names%20Rankin%20County%20Sheriff%20Bryan%20Bailey%20and%20six%20county-jail%20employees%20as%20defendants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rankin%20County%20Sheriff's%20Department%20has%20a%20history%20of%20violent%20interactions%20that%20have%20drawn%20both%20the%20national%20media's%20and%20federal%20authorities'%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20five%20men%20in%20the%20department's%20custody%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Finsider-probes-deaths-related-to-1-mississippi-sheriffs-office-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20died%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported%2C%20and%20the%20department's%20been%20under%20considerable%20scrutiny%20since%20several%20deputies%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20torturing%20two%20Black%20men%20in%20August.%20A%20recent%20investigation%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmississippitoday.org%2F2023%2F11%2F30%2Frankin-county-sheriff-goon-squad-got-away-with-years-of-brutality%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20dozens%20of%20other%20victims%20of%20abuse%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20department%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20string%20of%20controversies%2C%20the%20sheriff%20has%20yet%20to%20face%20any%20consequences%20and%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmississippi-sheriff-bryan-bailey-rankin-county-goon-squad-election-2023-11%23%3A~%3Atext%3DRankin%2520County%2520Sheriff%2520Bryan%2520Bailey%2Ccalling%2520for%2520Bailey%2520to%2520resign.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20reelected%20in%20November%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20running%20unopposed.%20Bailey%20has%20previously%20said%20there's%20no%20way%20he%20can%20monitor%20the%20behavior%20of%20everyone%20in%20his%20department%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20behavior%20of%20the%20five%20convicted%20deputies%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20called%20themselves%20the%20%26quot%3BGoon%20Squad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20case%20of%20Christopher%20Ray%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Carson's%20lawsuit%2C%20police%20took%20Ray%20to%20the%20Rankin%20County%20jail%20on%20October%2031%2C%202020%2C%20after%20his%20bail-bond%20company%20turned%20him%20in.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Ray%20had%20an%20outstanding%20warrant%20for%20failing%20to%20appear%20in%20court%20for%20a%20drug%20charge%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJail%20employees%20first%20put%20Ray%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bsegregation%20pod%26quot%3B%20to%20comply%20with%20COVID-19%20protocols%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20says%20that%20a%20few%20days%20later%2C%20jail%20employees%20moved%20him%20to%20a%20different%20cell%20and%20placed%20him%20on%20medical%20watch%20after%20he%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20complications%20from%20drug%20withdrawal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficers%20monitored%20Ray%20using%20cameras%20inside%20his%20new%20cell%20and%20described%20him%20as%20%26quot%3Banxious%20and%20depressed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20states.%20According%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20Ray%20first%20attempted%20suicide%20on%20November%208%2C%20when%20he%20tried%20to%20kill%20himself%20in%20the%20jail%20shower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20says%20that%20after%20the%20first%20attempt%2C%20Ray%20returned%20to%20his%20monitored%20cell%20and%20attempted%20suicide%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERay's%20second%20suicide%20attempt%20was%20inside%20a%20cell%20monitored%20by%20video%2024-7.%20According%20to%20the%20suit%2C%20he%20remained%20unresponsive%20inside%20his%20cell%20for%2044%20minutes%20before%20any%20jail%20staff%20intervened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20that%20%26quot%3Bsome%20or%20all%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20named%20defendants%20witnessed%20Ray's%20first%20suicide%20attempt%20and%20talked%20about%20it%20afterward.%20One%20lieutenant%20said%20jail%20employees%20took%20no%20measures%20to%20reduce%20Ray's%20risk%20to%20himself%20because%20they%20thought%20he%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bpussy%26quot%3B%20and%20wouldn't%20try%20to%20kill%20himself%20a%20second%20time%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20defendants%20who%20witnessed%20Ray's%20first%20suicide%20attempt%20also%20did%20not%20report%20or%20document%20the%20failed%20attempt%20and%20did%20not%20try%20to%20provide%20Ray%20medical%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Ray%20was%20transported%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20also%20says%20Bailey%20told%20Ray's%20mother%20that%20his%20second%20suicide%20attempt%20came%20after%20midnight%20on%20November%209%2C%20which%20the%20complaint%20says%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeliberate%20falsehood%26quot%3B%20meant%20to%20%26quot%3Bdeflect%20the%20suspicion%20of%20any%20misconduct%20by%20his%20detention%20officers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERay%20died%20in%20the%20hospital%20on%20November%2010%2C%202020%2C%20according%20to%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarson's%20lawsuit%20accuses%20the%20sheriff's%20department%20of%20having%20a%20%26quot%3Bculture%26quot%3B%20of%20ignoring%20its%20detainees'%20and%20inmates'%20known%20health%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20the%20sheriff's%20department%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20ignoring%20medical%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20deadly%20history%20at%20the%20Rankin%20County%20Sheriff's%20Department%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202021%2C%20Cory%20Jackson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmississippi-man-died-strapped-in-a-restraint-chair-while-hallucinating-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edied%20in%20the%20Rankin%20County%20jail%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Jackson's%20family%20previously%20told%20BI%20they%20were%20taking%20him%20to%20the%20hospital%20during%20a%20mental-he