ratiya%20Janata%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20highlighted%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwholesale%20reference%20to%20the%20President%2C%E2%80%9D%20of%20bills%20by%20the%20Kerala%20governor%2C%20noting%20that%20in%20such%20an%20event%2C%20the%20legislative%20activity%20of%20the%20state%20comes%20to%20a%20standstill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20third%20disturbing%20fact%20that%20we%20found%20this%20year%2C%20is%20a%20Governor%20of%20a%20traditionally%20minority%20government%20State%2C%20Kerala%2C%20sitting%20over%20bills%20for%20periods%20of%20up%20to%2023%20months.%20When%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20rapped%20him%20on%20his%20knuckles%2C%20what%20did%20he%20do%3F%20There%20were%208%20such%20bills.%20One%20bill%20was%20assented%20to%2C%207%20were%20referred%20to%20the%20President%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Nariman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20he%20is%20looking%20forward%20to%20a%20day%20when%20only%20independent%20persons%20will%20be%20favoured%20for%20these%20roles%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20waiting%20for%20the%20day%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20lay%20down%20that%20%E2%80%98look%2C%20it%20is%20only%20independent%20functionaries%20who%20are%20supposed%20to%20fill%20these%20great%20offices.%20Not%20the%20kind%20of%20people%20that%20we%20find%20today%2C%20like%20in%20Kerala%2C%20where%20wholesale%2C%20after%20you%20slept%20over%20the%20bills%2C%20you%20just%20give%20them%20back%20to%20the%20President.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nariman%E2%80%99s%20highlighting%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-kashmir-article-370-verdict%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Article%20370%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20it%20upheld%20the%20constitutional%20order%20that%20read%20down%20the%20article%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0was%20most%20scathing.%20He%20said%20it%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctremendous%20impact%20on%20federalism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20noted%20that%20there%20was%20a%20key%20intent%20behind%20bifurcating%20the%20state%20when%20there%20was%20already%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%20imposted%20%E2%80%93%20to%20bypass%20the%20clause%20in%20Article%20356%20which%20says%20that%20such%20a%20rule%20cannot%20exceed%20one%20year%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20national%20emergency%20or%20the%20Election%20Commission%20says%20that%20elections%20are%20not%20possible%20to%20be%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Article%20356%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20if%20a%20state%20government%20is%20unable%20to%20function%20according%20to%20constitutional%20provisions%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20take%20direct%20control%20of%20the%20state%20machinery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nariman%20called%20the%20solution%20found%20by%20the%20government%20%E2%80%9Cingenious%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20he%20criticised%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20skipping%20this%20key%20question%20in%20its%20decision%2C%20based%20on%20an%20undertaking%20given%20by%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20that%20statehood%20will%20be%20restored.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Solicitor%20General%20does%20not%20have%20any%20authority%20to%20bind%20the%20successor%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20noted%2C%20citing%20his%20own%20disavowal%20of%20such%20a%20statement%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EShreya%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ESinghal%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20criticised%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnearly%20four%20years%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20decision%20took%20to%20arrive%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20move%20took%20place%20in%202019%2C%20which%20is%20when%20the%20petitions%20were%20filed%20and%20that%20there%20has%20been%20no%20democratically%20elected%20government%20in%20the%20region%20for%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FLg4VHsnU1aw%3Fsi%3DzO4gz049Tfd6ISJg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702718312000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F16144643%2FUntitled-design-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-nariman-speech-election-commission-article-370-supreme-court-bbc-media%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delivering%20the%20Smt%20Bansari%20Sheth%20Endowment%20Lecture%2C%20the%20judge%20noted%20that%20four%20%26quot%3Bmost%20disturbing%26quot%3B%20things%20have%20happened%20in%20the%20country%20this%20year%20itself.%C2%A0He%20also%20was%20severely%20critical%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20recent%20judgement%20on%20the%20Centre's%20J%26amp%3BK%20decision.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A69%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-nariman-speech-election-commission-article-370-supreme-court-bbc-media%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inform%20Panel%20of%20Steps%20To%20Secure%20Places%20of%20Worship%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20Tells%20Manipur%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0The%20Supreme%20Court%20Friday%20asked%20the%20Manipur%20government%20to%20inform%20the%20Justice%20Gita%20Mittal%20Committee%20about%20the%20steps%20it%20has%20taken%20to%20secure%20places%20of%20worship%20that%20were%20destroyed%20in%20the%20ethnic%20clashes%20that%20have%20roiled%20the%20state%20for%20more%20than%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Finform-panel-of-steps-taken-to-secure-places-of-worship-sc-to-manipur-9070194%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20bench%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20and%20Justices%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20was%20told%20by%20the%20Manipur%20government%20that%20it%20has%20identified%20the%20places%20of%20worship%20that%20were%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%20during%20the%20clashes.%20The%20bench%20asked%20the%20government%20to%20provide%20a%20list%20of%20these%20places%20to%20the%20committee%20within%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetails%20of%20all%20places%20of%20worship%2C%20irrespective%20of%20religious%20denomination%20and%20the%20nature%20of%20such%20structures%2C%20which%20have%20been%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%20should%20be%20identified%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20was%20also%20permitted%20by%20the%20court%20to%20prepare%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccomprehensive%20proposal%2C%20including%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20places%20of%20worship%20which%20were%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%E2%80%9D%20and%20extended%20its%20term%20by%20six%20months%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuzefa%20Ahmadi%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Meitei%20Christian%20Churches%20Council%2C%20said%20the%20court%20should%20direct%20the%20Manipur%20government%20to%20make%20arrangements%20so%20that%20Christians%20can%20congregate%20for%20Christmas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVibha%20Datta%20Makhija%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20committee%2C%20said%20the%20panel%20%E2%80%9Chad%20visited%20and%20found%20that%20religious%20and%20non-religious%20buildings%20have%20suffered%20large%20degree%20of%20damage.%20Religious%20places%20were%20of%20various%20faiths%20including%20some%20Buddhist%20temples.%20Therefore%20we%20had%20asked%20the%20state%20to%20make%20a%20list%20of%20damaged%20places%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20was%20assured%20by%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20and%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%20that%20the%20Manipur%20go