2%80%99s%20Shattering%20Masterpiece%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F16132438%2FScreenshot-2023-12-16-at-1.23.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20released%2030%20years%20ago%2C%20remains%20Steven%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0108052%2Fawards%2F%5C%22%3Ehighly%20acclaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20emotionally%20sapping%20film.%20Winning%20seven%20Academy%20Awards%2C%20including%20Best%20Picture%20and%20Best%20Director%2C%20it%20was%20widely%20praised%20for%20its%20portrayal%20of%20the%20horrors%20of%20the%20Holocaust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%20marked%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20career.%20The%20director%20later%20said%20making%20the%20film%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnofilmschool.com%2Fschindlers-list-american-history%5C%22%3Echanged%20his%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUp%20to%20this%20point%2C%20he%20was%20known%20as%20a%20thrilling%20blockbuster%20director.%20With%20%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Spielberg%20turned%20his%20attention%20to%20darker%2C%20conflicted%20characters%20and%20shifted%20his%20focus%20to%20bigger%20themes%20of%20good%20and%20evil%2C%20heroism%20in%20adversity%20and%20the%20human%20cost%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20later%20work%20is%20still%20exciting%20and%20still%20jolts%20the%20senses%20in%20ways%20that%20very%20few%20contemporary%20filmmakers%20can%2C%20as%20in%20the%20musical%20showmanship%20of%20%3Cem%3EWest%20Side%20Story%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2021)%20or%20the%20fantastical%20realism%20of%20%3Cem%3EWar%20Horse%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011).%20But%20%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%20outshines%20them%20all%20with%20its%20detached%20focus%20on%20the%20sheer%20brutality%20and%20its%20steadfast%20refusal%20to%20look%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FgG22XNhtnoY%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetelling%20the%20Holocaust%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%20tells%20the%20true%20story%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fencyclopedia.ushmm.org%2Fcontent%2Fen%2Farticle%2Foskar-schindler%5C%22%3EOskar%20Schindler%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20German%20businessman%20who%20saved%201%2C100%20Jews%20from%20the%20Holocaust%20by%20employing%20them%20in%20his%20enamelware%20and%20ammunition%20factories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20accounts%20of%20the%20Holocaust%20on%20film%20had%20been%20reserved%20for%20documentary%2C%20such%20as%20Alain%20Resnais%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ENight%20and%20Fog%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1956)%20and%20Claude%20Lanzmann%E2%80%99s%20monumental%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ushmm.org%2Fcollections%2Fthe-museums-collections%2Fcollections-highlights%2Fclaude-lanzmann-shoah%5C%22%3EShoah%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1985)%2C%20which%20lasts%20nine%20hours%20and%20was%20composed%20of%20interviews%20with%20survivors%20and%20perpetrators%20of%20the%20Nazi%20death%20camps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHollywood%20had%20always%20shied%20away%20from%20dramatising%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20feeling%20such%20a%20devastating%20subject%20could%20not%20be%20depicted%20dramatically%20in%20the%20name%20of%20entertainment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecounting%20historical%20events%20in%20film%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmuse.jhu.edu%2Farticle%2F238611%2Fpdf%5C%22%3Efraught%20with%20tension%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Creative%20liberties%20are%20taken%2C%20timelines%20are%20condensed%2C%20characters%20combined%20and%20fictional%20elements%20added%20to%20enhance%20the%20dramatic%20quality%20of%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FW9vj2Wf57rQ%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpielberg%20acquired%20the%20rights%20to%20Thomas%20Keneally%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebookerprizes.com%2Fthe-booker-library%2Ffeatures%2Fthomas-keneally-on-how-he-wrote-schindlers-ark-i-knew-where-the-good%5C%22%3EBooker%20Prize-winning%20novel%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201983%2C%20but%20was%20initially%20reluctant%20to%20take%20on%20the%20film.%20Instead%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcollider.com%2Fsteven-spielberg-schindlers-list-martin-scorsese%2F%5C%22%3Eoffered%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20likes%20of%20Billy%20Wilder%20and%20Martin%20Scorsese.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20dismayed%20by%20what%20he%20perceived%20as%20a%20rising%20tide%20of%20anti-Semitism%20and%20Holocaust%20denial%2C%20Spielberg%20understood%20it%20was%20finally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgoldenglobes.com%2Farticles%2Fout-of-the-archives-1993-steven-spielberg-on-schindlers-list%2F%5C%22%3Etime%20to%20make%20the%20film%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20containing%20a%20few%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fschindlerslisteight.wordpress.com%2Fhistorical-accuracy%2Finaccuracies%2F%5C%22%3Ehistorical%20inaccuracies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20instrumental%20in%20creating%20what%20historian%20Peter%20Novick%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F4467615%5C%22%3EHolocaust%20consciousness%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20anti-Spielberg%20film%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpielberg%20wanted%20to%20avoid%20casting%20stars.%20He%20picked%20the%20then%20largely%20unknown%20Liam%20Neeson%20as%20the%20charismatic%20Schindler%20and%20Ralph%20Fiennes%20as%20Amon%20G%C3%B6th%2C%20the%20vicious%20SS%20commandant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20film%20details%20the%20personal%20interactions%20between%20the%20two%20men%20as%20Schindler%20observes%20the%20cruelties%20visited%20upon%20Polish%20Jews%20and%20sacrifices%20his%20fortune%20to%20save%20as%20many%20of%20them%20as%20he%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20over%20three%20hours%20long%2C%20%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%20remains%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20longest%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20director%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheasc.com%2Farticles%2Fschindlers-list-finds-heroism-amidst-holocaust%5C%22%3Etrademark%20flourishes%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20absent.%20There%20are%20no%20zooms%20or%20dolly%20shots%2C%20no%20smooth%20Steadicam%20tracking%20shots%20or%20soaring%20soundtrack.%20Apart%20from%20a%20brief%20opening%20and%20coda%2C%20the%20film%20remains%20the%20only%20black%20and%20white%20film%20Spielberg%20has%20ever%20shot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20his%20trusted%20cinematographer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DAlFOBCxZwKs%5C%22%3EJanusz%20Kami%C5%84ski%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20wanted%20the%20film%20to%20resemble%20archival%20footage.%20But%20the%20choice%20of%20black%20and%20white%20did%20not%20just%20suggest%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20past%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20suited%20the%20sober%20approach%20to%20the%20unfolding%20of%20devastating%20historical%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFamously%2C%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20centrepiece%20%E2%80%93%20a%20shattering%2015-minute%20scene%20in%20which%20the%20Nazis%20ferociously%20liquidate%20the%20Krak%C3%B3w%20ghetto%20%E2%80%93%20contains%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20only%20use%20of%20colour.%20As%20Schindler%20looks%20on%20in%20horror%2C%20he%20spots%20a%20young%20girl%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscreenrant.com%2Fschindlers-list-girl-red-coat-meaning-explained%2F%5C%22%3Ered%20raincoat%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20marks%20a%20radical%20turning%20point%20in%20Schindler%E2%80%99s%20moral%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fj1VL-y9JHuI%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpielberg%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20cross-cutting%20is%20meticulous.%20A%20mass%20killing%20scene%20is%20interspersed%20with%20footage%20of%20an%20SS%20officer%20playing%20Bach%20on%20a%20piano.%20In%20another%2C%20Schindler%20celebrates%20his%20birthday%20while%20G%C3%B6th%20beats%20his%20maid%20and%20a%20wedding%20takes%20place%20inside%20a%20labour%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpielberg%20shot%20on%20location%20just%20outside%20Auschwitz%20in%20the%20winter%20of%201992%20during%20the%20day%2C%20and%20at%20night%20worked%20on%20the%20post-production%20for%20%3Cem%3EJurassic%20Park%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20he%20had%20shot%20in%20Hawaii%20six%20months%20earlier.%20Spielberg%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Few.com%2Foscars%2F2018%2F04%2F27%2Fsteven-spielberg-schindlers-list-jurassic-park-tribeca-film-festival%2F%5C%22%3Eworking%20on%20two%20epoch-defining%20films%20simultaneously%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20yet%20they%20were%20completely%20different%20in%20tone%2C%20visual%20style%20and%20cultural%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECritical%20acclaim%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20reproach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20was%20widely%20praised%20on%20its%20release.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rogerebert.com%2Freviews%2Fschindlers-list-1993%5C%22%3ERoger%20Ebert%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20it%20the%20best%20Spielberg%20had%20ever%20made.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tampabay.com%2Farchive%2F1994%2F01%2F04%2Fschindler-has-a-fan-in-president%2F%5C%22%3EBill%20Clinton%3C%2Fa%3E%20implored%20audiences%20to%20see%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20also%20cond