Bridge%20of%20Spies%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2015).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpielberg%20has%20not%20entirely%20turned%20his%20back%20on%20his%20blockbuster%20entertainment%20roots.%20%3Cem%3EWar%20of%20the%20Worlds%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2005)%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Adventure%20of%20Tintin%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%20and%20%3Cem%3EReady%20Player%20One%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2018)%20all%20remind%20us%20of%20%E2%80%9Cearly%20Spielberg%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20the%20film%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F1994%2F03%2F21%2Fsteven-spielberg-profile-schindlers-list%5C%22%3Efinally%20convinced%20Hollywood%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20take%20Spielberg%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20message%20of%20courage%20in%20the%20face%20of%20tyranny%20seems%20just%20as%20relevant%20today%20as%20it%20was%2030%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20would%20have%20another%20role%20to%20play%20for%20Spielberg.%20When%20he%20returned%20to%20college%20in%202002%20to%20complete%20a%20bachelor%20of%20arts%20he%20had%20started%20%E2%80%93%20but%20never%20finished%20%E2%80%93%20in%201969%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-2002-may-31-me-graduate31-story.html%5C%22%3Esubmitted%20%3Cem%3ESchindler%E2%80%99s%20List%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20course%20credit.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F203234%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBen%20McCann%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20associate%20professor%20of%20French%20Studies%2C%20University%20of%20Adelaide.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F